When you get serious about your life goals
https://t.co/WiLwZTB8EM

You're going to lose a lot of friends.

That's why a supercar has two seats and a bus has 30.

As you grow and evolve, you'll find that your priorities shift, and your circle of friends may change. 

Some may drift away, unable to align with your newfound purpose.

While others will stand by your side, supporting you through thick and thin.

Remember that quality always trumps quantity when it comes to friendships. 

Cherish those who believe in your vision and encourage your growth. 

They are the true companions on your journey to success.

They don't see the long hours you're putting in, doing the same thing over and over until you get it right.

You're grinding every day, investing your time and effort into a vision that you can't get out of your head, with no guarantee that it's ever going to work. 

There's no applause, no instant recognition.

But here's the truth:

One day, you're going to look back and know that this is why you made it. 

You didn't get lucky, you sacrificed for it. 

The silent dedication, the relentless pursuit of your dreams, and the unwavering belief in yourself will be your ultimate reward. 

Keep going.

Your hard work will pay off.

There's a quote from past times that goes like this:
https://t.co/WiLwZTB8EM

To wisely live your life you don't need to know much.

Just remember two main rules for the beginning.

1. You better be hungry than eat whatever.
2. And better be alone than with whoever.

Let me tell you a secret.

One rule that many overlook when they begin their journey: 

Ideas don't come out fully formed; they only become clear as you work on them. You just have to get started.

Too often, we wait for that perfect idea, that flawless plan, or that ideal moment to begin.

But the truth is, clarity emerges from action. 

When you take that first step, when you start working on your ideas, they begin to take shape, evolve, and refine themselves.

It's like sculpting a masterpiece; you start with a block of marble, and it's through the chiseling and shaping that the true beauty is revealed.

ğŸ’¦The wetland is renowned for its rich biodiversity, particularly its birdlife. It is home to a diverse range of bird species, including migratory birds. The park is especially known for being a habitat for the rare and endemic bird species known as the "bird of paradise."
